<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">Given N classes and M group slots, there are M^N different group combinations.
<br />

<br />
With as few as 5 classes and groups of size 5, that's 3,125 different group combinations.
<br />

<br />
You want all of these group combinations to be both interesting and equally effective?
<br />

<br />
You could do this by making classes vanilla.
<br />

<br />
Warrior: heals himself by using 'endurance' to prevent damage.  Can take damage.  Does damage
<br />

<br />
Mage: heals pets by using 'mana' to prevent damage.  Pets can take damage, if they die the mage does.  Does damage
<br />

<br />
Lich: posseses monsters.  As a monster, can take damage.  Does damage, and protects the vessel which it occupies.  Switching vessels is hard and cannot be done in emergencies.
<br />

<br />
Rogue: uses luck to avoid damage.  Can take damage.  Does damage
<br />

<br />
The same class, repeated 4 times, but with flavour differences.  Is that what you are looking for?</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
